{'name': 'Lionel Messi'}.response: Lionel Messi, born on June 24, 1987, in Rosario, Argentina, is a professional footballer who plays as a forward for Paris Saint-Germain and the Argentina national team. Known for his extraordinary dribbling skills, vision, and scoring ability, Messi is considered one of the greatest footballers of all time. He has won numerous awards throughout his career, including the FIFA Ballon d'Or multiple times. Messi began his professional career with Barcelona, where he spent over 20 years, before moving to Paris Saint-Germain in 2021.
